Two dozen schoolchildren were injured one seriously in a minibus crash near Durban on Tuesday morning.All the children were take to hospital.The minibus was traveling from Sundumbile to Mandeni on the KwaZulu-Natal north coast when the driver lost control. It rear-ended an empty taxi which in turn hit another vehicle. IPSS Medical Rescue paramedic Paul Herbst said 24 children were taken to hospital.Injuries ranged from minor to serious.Herbst said a child trapped in the front of the minibus carrying the children had to be carefully removed from the vehicle. She had been seriously hurt. 